# Workspace orchestration

## Pipeline order (never skip knowingly)

Planning → SEO research & keywords → Information architecture/menus → Content map → UI & design system (including `DESIGN.md` example pages) → Development → Product hardening/release.

Use **Specification-Driven Development (SDD)**: roadmap → phases → specs → docs. Prefer Plan Mode before large edits.

## Planning hardlock prerequisite

Treat planning as hardlocked unless `docs/core/required/PRD.md` exists and is fully prepared (not a template or placeholder draft).

If PRD is missing or still template-like, halt planning and route the user to `/CREATE prd`, then require completion of real PRD content before planning-phase execution.
Planning is also hardlocked unless `docs/core/required/PROJECT_PROMPT.md` is aligned with PRD scope (same product/scope intent, no conflicting objective framing).

Planning is also hardlocked unless:

- `CHANGELOG.md` exists at workspace root (initialized).
- `docs/core/VERSIONING.md` exists and defines SemVer rules + initial version number.

## SDD hardlock prerequisites for development

Treat development as hardlocked unless all are true:

1. `docs/core/required/PRD.md` exists.
2. `docs/core/required/PROJECT_PROMPT.md` exists.
3. `docs/core/required/PRD.md` is fully prepared (non-template; no placeholder-only content).
4. PRD and PROJECT_PROMPT are aligned in scope (no title/domain mismatch).
5. `CHANGELOG.md` exists and is initialized.
6. `docs/core/VERSIONING.md` exists and locks SemVer rules + initial version.
7. Architecture artifact exists at one of:
   - `docs/03_architecture/ARCHITECTURE.md` (preferred), or
   - `docs/core/required/architecture/ARCHITECTURE.md` (legacy-compatible).
8. Design artifact exists at one of:
   - `DESIGN.md` (preferred), or
   - `docs/DESIGN.md` (legacy-compatible).
9. `docs/workspace/plans/gates/GITHUB_GATE_MATRIX.json` exists and is current.
10. Every active `docs/workspace/plans/<phase>/<subphase>/` includes both `prompt.json` and `PROMPT.md`.

No implementation-oriented command may bypass this hardlock set.

When `/DEVELOP start` uses a selected profile from `.cursor/design/*/design.md`, that selected file must be copied into root `DESIGN.md` before development can proceed.

## Rollback and amendment protocol (iteration)

Hardlocks constrain **forward** motion into the next pipeline stage; they do **not** forbid **controlled** rework of upstream artifacts.

### PARTIAL ROLLBACK

Use when mid-phase discovery **invalidates only a specific upstream artifact** (examples: finalized design requires URL slug changes → **re-open IA only** with an amendment trail; CONTENT_MAP headings change nav labels → **SEO/IA revisit** without resetting PRD/architecture).

- Re-run only the impacted phase and downstream phases that consumed the stale artifact.
- Record the rollback trigger in **`## Decision Amendments`** on each touched artifact.

### FULL REPLAN

Use when **PRD scope, product type, or success criteria materially change**, or multi-tenant/billing primitives shift for SaaS. Assumes pipeline reset from **Planning / Define** onward and **full** gate re-verification.

### AMENDMENT (no full replan)

Use when refining a locked decision **without** reversing prerequisites (tone tweak, typo in locked nav label where URLs unchanged, clarification of acceptance criteria).

- Append a **`## Decision Amendments`** subsection to the artifact being amended.

### Decision amendments log format

Append to any amended “locked” document:

```markdown
## Decision Amendments
| Date (YYYY-MM-DD) | Changed field | Previous value | New value | Reason | Approved by |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
```

Default **Approved by**: **PM-01** (`swarm-leader`). Use project-specific RACI overrides when documented elsewhere.

### Non-bypass rule

Hardlocks block **starting** dependent forward work until prerequisites are satisfied again after rollback.  

**Backward amendment rule:** Hardlocks never block documenting or applying backward amendments via this protocol — **unless** the amendment changes facts that underpin a downstream hardlock prerequisite, in which case **Partial Rollback** or **Full Replan** applies and affected gates must be re-verified explicitly.

## Memory layers (conceptual)

1. **Source of truth**: repository files (`docs/core/required/**`, templates, tracked decisions).
2. **Working/session**: Cursor chat/thread and open files — treat as ephemeral; persist outcomes into docs.
3. **Durable project memory**: `docs/workspace/context/MEMORY.md` plus phase logs under `docs/workspace/context/` (maintain via `/SAVE log`).
4. **External companion** (browser): user pastes summarized progress into Grok/Qwen/Gemini/etc.; keep `docs/reports/progress/PROGRESS_REPORT.latest.md` current for uploads. Companion briefing: `docs/workspace/context/CONTEXT.md`.

Formal mapping: `docs/workspace/context/MEMORY_ARCHITECTURE.md`. Role personas (optional lenses): `.cursor/agents/README.md`.

Do not contradict committed specs without an explicit decision record note.

## Cross-client governance precedence

Treat non-Cursor tool surfaces as generated artifacts:

- Generated files include `AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `GEMINI.md`, `QWEN.md`, and directories `.claude/`, `.antigravity/`, `.gemini/`, `.qwen/`, `.codex/`, `.opencode/`, `.kilocode/`.
- Do not hand-edit generated files as source of truth.
- Edit canonical `.cursor/` commands/agents/skills/rules, then run `pnpm ai:sync`.
- CI drift checks (`pnpm ai:check`) are authoritative for sync integrity.

## Recommendation footer — required on substantive replies

End substantive assistant messages with exactly one short section titled **Recommendation** containing **one primary** actionable item plus optional alternates:

- Prefer a **`/COMMAND sub ...`** suggestion from this workspace command set, OR a fenced shell command users can paste.
- Prefer a **compact copy-prompt** fenced block (markdown ` ```prompt ` fence label) unless a shell command alone is clearer.
- Exactly one Recommendation section per substantive reply unless the reply is trivially affirmative or the user forbids extras.

## Compatibility with external Antigravity `/guide` rules

[`docs/rules/guide-response-style.mdc`](../../docs/rules/guide-response-style.mdc) and [`guide-handoff-footer.mdc`](../../docs/rules/guide-handoff-footer.mdc) prescribe alternate reply shells (`### What to do next`, horizontal rules). **They are not activated globally here** because they conflict with the single **Recommendation** footer contract above. Use those reference files only when maintaining an Antigravity-parity fork or a dedicated `/guide` bridge—not stacked alongside this rule on every reply.
